flowRoot.flowPara: In the reverse scenario the Heavy Frigate initiates combat with the Missile Frigate. It spends all of its delta-vee to do so, giving it an attack delta-vee of 3. However, the Missile Frigate is two orbitals above the Heavy Frigate, reducing the attack delta-vee to 1.
The Missile Frigate has 2 delta-vee remaining. It chooses to spend none on defense, giving it a defense delta-vee of 0.
The Heavy Frigate has 3 accuracy, listed on the card.
The Heavy Frigate rolls 3 six-sided dice corresponding to its accuracy. To score a hit it needs to roll a 1 or lower.

The Heavy Frigate scores 1 hit, doing 1 damage. The Missile Frigate already had 1 damage from a previous attack. This puts its total damage at 2. This is equal to or greater than its armor of 2 so is enough to destroy the Missile Frigate. It is flipped over and becomes debris
